The paper discusses the use of MultiLayer Perceptrons (MLPs) for microarray gene expression analysis, which is a problem in the field of bioinformatics. MLPs are a type of neural network, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning methods, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of MLPs for image classification is also mentioned, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the high dimensionality of the microarray data, which is a problem in the field of data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the use of evolutionary algorithms for optimizing the MLPs, which falls under the subfield of neural evolution (cs.NE).
